  "datePublished": "2023-09-04",
  "description": "So I\u0026rsquo;ve realized that while I quite like Ko-fi on the whole, I can\u0026rsquo;t stand its interface for adding new blog posts. And beside that, I\u0026rsquo;ve continued to get a trickle of new subscribers to my Substack - where I can also give out subscriptions, unlike Ko-Fi.\nMy current plan is to switch back to Substack for releasing my letters to the Web- using a mix of free and subscriber-only posting, while I\u0026rsquo;ll use Ko-fi for sharing garden images to folk who subscribe over there. (I\u0026rsquo;m also working on, like I\u0026rsquo;ve mentioned, re-starting my digital garden: access to that might be available as a subscription or one-time purchase, on Ko-fi, later, as well.)\n",
